  "text": "Because of the well known links between ␣-synuclein and dopamine dysfunction in Parkinson's disease, and the prominent expression and presynaptic localization of all three synuclein family members in dopaminergic neurons of the SNpc [data are available (see Notes)] [CITATION_1] , we performed in-depth studies on the midbrain dopaminergic systems of TKO mice.",
